Mug's Game.
well put.

The tout services that bought out of the money calls of high beta stocks based on "flow, "unusual call activity" (which is actually quite usual) and/or the charts - have blown up their clients. Not surprisingly, you will never ever hear about their losses -

we only here about winners. This is called selective (marketing) disclosure - it is illegal according to the SEC. The unaccountable offenders should be forewarned. Fugazzis all. Keep your children and portfolios away from these bloodsuckers.
